## 1. Purpose
This procedure defines how [COMPANY] periodically reviews and recertifies access entitlements to confirm they remain appropriate, least-privilege, and aligned to current business need. Recertification detects and removes access that has accumulated through role changes, missed offboarding, or scope creep, and produces the evidence assessors require.

## 2. Scope
Applies to access entitlements across all in-scope systems — the [IdP — e.g. Okta], [AWS] (IAM Identity Center / IAM), [Snowflake] (roles and grants), the [GitHub] organization, federated [SaaS] applications, and the production application — covering human users, service/non-human accounts, and privileged roles. Reviews give particular attention to access to PHI. This procedure operationalizes the review requirements of `access-control-policy.md.template`.

## 3. Frequency
| Access type | Minimum review frequency |
|---|---|
| Privileged / administrative access (AWS root & admin, Snowflake ACCOUNTADMIN/SECURITYADMIN, GitHub org owners, IdP super-admins) | [Quarterly] |
| Access to PHI / production data | [Quarterly] |
| Standard user access | [Semi-annually] |
| Service / non-human accounts | [Semi-annually] |
| Event-driven (org change, M&A, incident, audit finding) | As triggered |

## 4. Scope of Each Review & Reviewers
1. For each cycle, [IT / Security] **shall** generate an entitlement report per system from the authoritative source (IdP assignments, AWS IAM Identity Center / Access Analyzer, Snowflake `ACCOUNT_USAGE` grants and access-history views, GitHub team/member exports).
2. The **reviewer** for each entitlement is the relevant [System / Resource Owner] or [Manager] — i.e., someone with authority and knowledge to confirm business need. Reviewers **shall not** certify their own access.
3. Reviewers **shall** confirm each entitlement is still required, at the right level, and consistent with least privilege and SoD; PHI access is confirmed as minimum-necessary.
4. Reports **shall** be reconciled against HR records to surface accounts for terminated or moved personnel and orphaned/stale accounts.

## 5. Evidence
The following **shall** be retained for each cycle as audit evidence: the entitlement reports reviewed, reviewer identities and decisions (certify / revoke / modify), dates, the resulting revocation tickets, and confirmation of completed revocations. Evidence is retained per `../governance/document-control.md.template` (and at least six years where it relates to PHI access).

## 6. Revocation of Unneeded Access
1. Any entitlement marked **revoke** or **modify** **shall** generate a remediation ticket.
2. Revocations **shall** be completed within **[N business days]** of the review decision; privileged-access revocations within **[N business days / immediately]**.
3. Revocation is performed via the [IdP]/system-native controls (see the deprovisioning checklist in `joiner-mover-leaver-procedure.md.template`) and **shall** be confirmed and evidenced.
4. The cycle is **not complete** until all flagged access is remediated or formally risk-accepted via §7.

## 7. Exceptions
Where access flagged for removal must be retained, an exception **shall** be documented per `../governance/exceptions-and-waivers.md.template`, approved by the [Security Officer], time-bound, and recorded in the exceptions log.

## 8. Roles & Responsibilities
| Role | Responsibility |
|---|---|
| [Security Officer / CISO] | Owns this procedure; schedules cycles; ensures completion and evidence quality. |
| [IT / Identity Administrators] | Generate entitlement reports; execute and confirm revocations. |
| [System / Resource Owners] & [Managers] | Review and certify access within their domains; cannot self-certify. |
| Internal Audit | Independently verifies that reviews occurred and revocations completed. |

See `../governance/roles-and-responsibilities.md.template` for full role definitions.

## 9. Compliance, Monitoring & Enforcement
Completion of each cycle within schedule is tracked as a control metric and reported in management review (`../governance/management-review.md.template`). Overdue reviews and unremediated revocations are escalated. Patterns of excess access feed back into role definitions and the SoD matrix. Violations are handled per `../people/hr-security-policy.md.template`.

